{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_011Ccwb5GMDTSnXk9Hfvq7DJ","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Nice — race conditions in fixture setup are especially nasty because they only show up under CI's concurrency and timing, so they're easy to dismiss as \"flaky\" and hard to reproduce locally. A lock around the shared file is the right call.\n\nOne thing worth a quick sanity check, if you haven't already: make sure the lock covers teardown too, not just setup. A common variant is that setup is now serialized but two tests still race on *cleaning up* the shared file (or one test tears down while another is mid-setup). Also worth confirming the lock is process-safe if your CI runs tests across multiple processes/workers — an in-process (thread) lock won't help there; you'd want a file lock (e.g. `flock` / `filelock`).\n\nWant me to take a look at the fixture code to double-check the lock's scope and that it holds across your CI's parallelism model?"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":5493,"cache_read_input_tokens":15171,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":5493},"output_tokens":2,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"151b9221-58ee-4469-8669-e57bc69e96b7","uuid":"ce82a6ea-b25f-4d73-9336-bfc48adbf6fc","request_id":"req_011Ccwb5FYr8a3aigzZGBAXw"}
